Setup for the test case presented in Bordbar et al.(2014) article.

For more details see "A line by line based weighted sum of gray gases 
model for inhomogeneous CO2–H2O mixture in oxy-fired combustion".
doi: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.combustflame.2014.03.013

Replace the functions present in RTS_functions.f90 with those present in user_functions.f90

To facilitate post-processing, replace these lines in the output.rts file.
!===============================================================
!                     Lineup Variable Save               
!===============================================================
.true.   !on/off lineup save module (only for 3D simulations)
 1        !Method: 1-Point 2-Node
 2        !Number of Lineups
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
! Axis  >>   X:(x,a,b)   Y:(a,y,b)   Z:(a,b,z)                  !
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
!             CV Point         CV Node      Variable            !
! Axis      a        b        a       b        ID               !
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
   y      1.00d0   1.00d0     10      10        3 
   x      4.00d0   1.00d0     10      10        10

This test case was originally proposed by Liu (1999) with some minor 
modifications and later repeated by Potter (2010).

Modify the following lines in the input.rts file
   
  .true.     0.10d0    !CO2 mole fraction
  .true.     0.20d0    !H2O mole fraction
   
For more details see "Numerical Solutions of Three-Dimensional Non-Grey 
Gas Radiative Transfer Using the Statistical Narrow-Band Model"
doi: https://doi.org/10.1115/1.2825944

and "Evaluation of solution methods for radiative heat transfer in 
gaseous oxy-fuel combustion environments"
doi: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jqsrt.2010.04.028

To facilitate post-processing, replace these lines in the output.rts file.
!===============================================================
!                     Lineup Variable Save               
!===============================================================
.true.    !on/off lineup save module (only for 3D simulations)
 1        !Method: 1-Point 2-Node
 2        !Number of Lineups
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
! Axis  >>   X:(x,a,b)   Y:(a,y,b)   Z:(a,b,z)                  !
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
!             CV Point         CV Node      Variable            !
! Axis      a        b        a       b        ID               !
!---------------------------------------------------------------!
   y      1.00d0   1.00d0     10      10        3 
   y      1.00d0   2.00d0     10      10        10
